# Privacy Policy – Kivu Ride Ltd
**Effective Date:** 17/09/2025

**Company:** Kivu Ride Ltd  
**Contact:** KG 7 Ave, Kigali, Rwanda  
**Phone:** +250 789 195 753  
**Email:** kivuride250@gmail.com

## 1. Introduction
Kivu Ride Ltd (“we”, “our”, “us”) is committed to protecting the personal data of our riders,
corporate clients, drivers, and employees. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use,
store, and protect personal data in compliance with the Rwanda Personal Data Protection and
Privacy Law (Law No. 058/2021) and other applicable laws.

## 2. Data We Collect
- **Riders:** Name, phone number, email, payment info, trip history.  
- **Drivers:** Name, phone number, ID, driver’s license, vehicle details, payment info.  
- **Corporate Clients:** Organization info, staff contacts, billing details.  
- **Employees:** HR information.

## 3. Purpose of Processing
- Ride booking and management  
- Payments and subscriptions  
- Corporate billing and account management  
- Driver onboarding and compliance  
- Communications and support

## 4. Legal Basis
- Consent of the data subject  
- Contractual necessity  
- Legal obligation

## 5. Data Storage and Transfer
Personal data is securely stored on DigitalOcean cloud servers in
[Amsterdam, Netherlands / United States]. Where stored outside Rwanda,
safeguards are applied in line with GDPR and ISO 27001 standards.

## 6. Retention
We retain personal data only as long as necessary for services or legal obligations.

## 7. Security
- Encryption (in transit & at rest)  
- Role-based access controls  
- GDPR-compliant cloud hosting  
- Regular audits and backups

## 8. Rights of Data Subjects
- Access, correct, or delete data  
- Withdraw consent  
- Request portability  
- File a complaint with NCSA / DPO

## 9. Third Parties
We share data only with trusted providers (e.g., payment gateways, SMS, hosting) to deliver our services.

## 10. Contact Us (DPO)
**Data Protection Officer – Kivu Ride Ltd**  
Phone: +250 789 195 753  
Email: kivuride250@gmail.com

